  "response_text": "This is a balanced, whole-food-based diet plan designed for healthy, sustainable weight loss (approximately 1-2 lbs per week). It focuses on **calorie control, high protein, high fiber, and healthy fats** to keep you full and preserve muscle mass.\n\n**Important Note:** Calorie needs vary. This plan is based on approximately **1,500 calories per day**, which is a common target for many women. Men or very active individuals may need 1,800–2,000 calories. **Consult a doctor or dietitian before starting any weight loss plan.**\n\n---\n\n### The Core Principles (The \"Rules\")\n\n1.  **Protein at Every Meal:** Aim for 20-30g per meal (chicken, fish, tofu, eggs, Greek yogurt, beans).\n2.  **Fiber is Your Friend:** Fill half your plate with non-starchy vegetables (broccoli, spinach, peppers, cauliflower).\n3.  **Smart Carbs:** Choose complex carbs (quinoa, oats, sweet potatoes, brown rice) over refined (white bread, pasta, sugar).\n4.  **Healthy Fats:** Include small portions of avocado, nuts, seeds, or olive oil for satiety and hormone health.\n5.  **Hydrate:** Drink 8-10 glasses of water daily. Often, thirst is mistaken for hunger.\n6.  **No Liquid Calories:** Avoid soda, juice, sweetened coffee, and alcohol.\n\n---\n\n### Sample 7-Day Meal Plan\n\n*Portions are estimates. Adjust based on your hunger levels.*\n\n| Day | Breakfast ( ~300-350 cal) | Lunch ( ~400-450 cal) | Dinner ( ~450-500 cal) | Snack ( ~150 cal) |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Mon** | 2 scrambled eggs + 1 cup spinach + 1 slice whole-wheat toast | Large salad: 4 oz grilled chicken, mixed greens, cucumber, tomato, 2 tbsp vinaigrette | 4 oz baked salmon + 1 cup roasted broccoli + ½ cup quinoa | 1 small apple + 1 tbsp peanut butter |\n| **Tue** | 1 cup Greek yogurt (plain) + ½ cup berries + 1 tbsp chia seeds | Lettuce wraps: 4 oz ground turkey, bell peppers, lettuce cups + 1 cup carrot sticks | 4 oz lean steak + 1 cup sautéed zucchini + 1 small sweet potato | 1 hard-boiled egg + a handful of almonds (10-12) |\n| **Wed** | Green smoothie: 1 scoop protein powder, 1 cup spinach, ½ banana, 1 tbsp almond butter, unsweetened almond milk | 1 can tuna (in water) mixed with 1 tbsp avocado, served over a bed of greens + ½ cup cherry tomatoes | 4 oz baked chicken breast + 2 cups roasted Brussels sprouts + 1 tbsp balsamic glaze | 1 cup cucumber slices + ¼ cup hummus |\n| **Thu** | Overnight oats: ½ cup oats, 1 cup unsweetened almond milk, 1 tbsp flaxseed, ½ cup raspberries | Leftover chicken + Brussels sprouts from Wed | Stir-fry: 4 oz shrimp + 2 cups mixed veggies (broccoli, snap peas, bell peppers) + 1 tbsp soy sauce, no rice | 1 string cheese + 1 small pear |\n| **Fri** | 2 poached eggs + ½ avocado on 1 slice whole-grain toast | Quinoa bowl: ½ cup quinoa, 4 oz black beans, 1 cup mixed veggies, salsa, ¼ avocado | 4 oz baked cod + 1 cup steamed asparagus + 1 cup cauliflower \"rice\" | 1 cup mixed berries + 2 tbsp whipped cream (unsweetened) |\n| **Sat** | Protein pancake (1 scoop protein, 1 egg, ½ banana, blended) + 1 tbsp syrup | Open-faced sandwich: 1 slice rye bread, 4 oz smoked salmon, cream cheese, capers, and arugula | 4 oz lean ground beef + 1 cup zucchini noodles + ½ cup marinara sauce | 1 small handful of walnuts + 1 clementine |\n| **Sun** | 2 scrambled eggs + 1 cup sautéed mushrooms + 1 slice turkey bacon | Leftover beef + zoodles from Sat | \"Buddha Bowl\": 4 oz baked tofu, 1 cup roasted sweet potato, 1 cup kale, 2 tbsp tahini dressing | 1 cup low-fat cottage cheese + black pepper |\n\n---\n\n### Smart Snack Options (100-200 calories each)\n\n- **Veggies + Hummus:** 1 cup bell pepper/cucumber + 2 tbsp hummus.\n- **Protein Shake:** 1 scoop protein powder + water/unsweetened almond milk.\n- **Greek Yogurt + Berries:** ¾ cup plain Greek yogurt + ¼ cup blueberries.\n- **Apple + Nut Butter:** 1 small apple + 1 tbsp almond butter.\n- **Handful of Nuts:** ¼ cup almonds or walnuts.\n\n---\n\n### Foods to Eat (The \"YES\" List)\n\n- **Proteins:** Chicken breast, turkey, fish (salmon, tuna, cod), eggs, tofu, tempeh, legumes (lentils, chickpeas, black beans).\n- **Vegetables:** Leafy greens, broccoli, cauliflower, bell peppers, zucchini, asparagus, mushrooms, tomatoes, cucumbers.\n- **Fruits:** Berries, apples, pears, citrus fruits (limit bananas and grapes to small portions).\n- **Complex Carbs:** Oats, quinoa, brown rice, sweet potatoes, whole-grain bread, beans.\n- **Healthy Fats:** Avocado, olive oil, nuts, seeds, fatty fish.\n- **Dairy (optional):** Plain Greek yogurt, cottage cheese, low-fat milk.\n\n### Foods to Limit (The \"NO\" or \"Rarely\" List)\n\n- **Refined Carbs:** White bread, white pasta, white rice, pastries, crackers.\n- **Sugary Drinks:** Soda, juice, sweetened tea/coffee, sports drinks.\n- **Processed Foods:** Fast food, chips, frozen meals with high sodium, processed meats (sausage, bacon in excess).\n- **Added Sugars:** Candy, cookies, cake, ice cream, syrup.\n- **Alcohol:** Empty calories that slow metabolism and increase appetite.\n\n### Pro-Tips for Success\n\n1.  **Don't Skip Breakfast:** It regulates blood sugar and prevents overeating later.\n2.  **Eat Slowly:** It takes 20 minutes for your brain to register fullness. Put your fork down between bites.\n3.  **Meal Prep on Sunday:** Cook a batch of quinoa, chop veggies, and grill chicken for the week.\n4.  **Track for a Week:** Use an app like MyFitnessPal or Lose It! for 7 days to understand your portions. You don't have to do it forever.\n5.  **Listen to Your Body:** Eat until you are 80% full (satisfied",
